race.description: De Bortoli Wines Super Mdn Hcp
race.comment: NAIFAH (1) well-bred filly returning from a lengthy break. Had mixed luck in all three runs at Listed and Group 3 level. Fitted with the two searching trials and the booking of Tommy Berry is a good lead from the inside barrier. SPONARS (2) unwanted in betting on resumption when a fast finishing second from last on the turn over this course and distance. Will race much closer today from the inside gate. A repeat effort will see him go close. COMPOSED (3) covered plenty of ground in the run on debut when a gritty fourth over 1000m at this track. Will come on from that run and gets his chance. BARSANDBI (6) showed a ton of tenacity on resumption when gripping on late to run third over 900m at Newcastle. Has placed at this trip and is capable of taking a hand in the finish.
